				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What's the difference?<a name="36646"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 4:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well when I think about it, when would a bard profit from a 15% damage increase by a song, if he can twist in another DoT to have a dmg increase of 25% (twisting 4 insted of 3 plus Call of the Muse) or 20% (twisting 5 insted of 4 plus Call of the Muse dropping all the time in a 5 song twist). The only benefit I can see would be if the mob was highly resistant to certain damage types and you would boost the songs that dont get resisted. But this isn't the case that often. So all in all it is not that bad for the bard I think.
<br />
One more thing, I would like to add, just a minor thing really. To have CotM working, the Song has to be in effect for the DoTer all the time (like a worn focus effect). This means, the DoTer has to be in range of the song all the time and you have to keep the song up all the time, to get the full benefit from it. (Yes of course you have to do it anyway to get the full melee haste bonus, but generally in a grouping situation, I am closer to melees than to casters...). The same is true for DD casters, but there is a little difference: The DD casters can time their nukes to hit during the period they have Rizlona's/CotM up and have it dropped during the nonnuking time. I think this makes CotM a tiny little bit more efficient for DDs than for DoTs. Just a thought though. Of course it's great to have both damage types boosted. ;)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
